# Fluff Date: 2026-03-05 17:18:25
<overview>
<p>The Engineering Vehicle is a forty-ton tracked support platform produced by the New Earth Trading Company on New Earth. Introduced in 2570 during the final decades of the Age of War, the design was commissioned to provide military engineering units with a robust, affordable platform capable of performing construction, demolition, and obstacle clearance tasks in forward operating environments. Powered by an internal combustion engine rather than a costly fusion reactor, the vehicle offered commanders a practical and economical solution for the demanding logistical requirements of modern combined-arms warfare. Engineering Vehicles produced by the New Earth Trading Company became a common sight across the Inner Sphere, serving with armies of every major power for centuries.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Engineering Vehicle is built around a WorkHorse 240 internal combustion engine fitted with a PowerChain overdrive system that prevents motor burnout during sustained heavy equipment operation. This powerplant drives the tracked chassis to a cruising speed of 64 km/h with a top flank speed of 97 km/h, making the vehicle surprisingly quick for a construction platform. Communications are handled by a TharHes Caliope HM-10 system, though the vehicle mounts no dedicated targeting or tracking equipment, reflecting its non-combat design philosophy.</p><p>The standard configuration mounts a turret-mounted backhoe and a rear-mounted lift hoist, giving the crew the ability to excavate positions, remove obstacles, and recover damaged vehicles or salvageable components from the battlefield. The vehicle carries 2.5 tons of Basic Metal Plate Standard armor, sufficient to resist small arms fire and light shrapnel but inadequate against any serious military threat. The base model carries no weapons at all, leaving crews entirely dependent on escort forces for protection. While the oversized engine provides ample power for heavy equipment tasks, the reliance on an internal combustion powerplant means the vehicle cannot operate in vacuum or hostile atmospheric conditions without modification.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The Flamer variant is one of the oldest engineering vehicle configurations in service, mounting three Vehicle Flamers alongside a front-mounted backhoe. Two flamers are turret-mounted with a third facing forward, providing comprehensive coverage for vegetation clearance operations. This configuration is commonly deployed to burn away dense undergrowth, clear firing lanes, and prepare landing zones in heavily forested or overgrown terrain. The retention of the backhoe gives crews some limited earthmoving capability alongside their primary clearance role.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The New Earth Trading Company was one of the oldest interstellar commercial enterprises in human history, founded during the chaotic exploration era of the twenty-second century. Originally a transportation and trade firm, NETC expanded into robotics and military production over the following centuries, eventually becoming a significant defense contractor for the Terran Hegemony. The Engineering Vehicle was among their more modest products, but its simplicity and reliability ensured steady demand from military forces across the Inner Sphere.</p><p>Following the fall of the Star League, the New Earth factory passed through a brief period of independent operation before being absorbed into the Lyran Commonwealth. Production continued uninterrupted through the Succession Wars under Lyran and later Federated Commonwealth ownership, with the vehicle seeing service on virtually every front. One of the most notable uses of engineering vehicles in combat occurred during the Battle of Loric in 2978. The Twelfth Star Guards had broken through Free Worlds League lines while attempting to relieve elements of the Eridani Light Horse, but found additional Marik forces guarding a river crossing. The Guards' engineering company immediately began constructing a pontoon bridge under constant harassment from aerospace fighters and Long Tom artillery. Three bridges were destroyed before completion, and the engineering company was nearly wiped out, but the final vehicle managed to finish the crossing before being destroyed, allowing the Guards to reach the beleaguered Light Horse forces.</p><p>The Twelfth Star Guards' engineering unit, known as "El Magnifico's Engineering Company," was renowned as one of the finest combat engineer formations in the Inner Sphere. The Eighty-first Combat Engineers of the Federated Suns also earned distinction with these vehicles, particularly during the Second Succession War when Captain Wedge Donovan used engineering vehicles and explosives to halt an entire Capellan column in the mountains on Atlas, destroying a full company of BattleMechs before his own vehicle was lost.</p><p>The Word of Blake seized control of New Earth during the Jihad, and the subsequent liberation campaign during Operation SCOUR proved devastating to the planet's industrial base. Orbital bombardment and fierce ground combat left little industry intact, and the New Earth Trading Company facility was almost certainly destroyed. Production of the Engineering Vehicle ceased, and the factory has remained inactive from the early Republic era onward.</p>
</history>

